 To specify how many GPUs a Serve deployment needs, you can use the `ray_actor_options` parameter in the `@serve.deployment` decorator and set the `"num_gpus"` key to the desired number of GPUs. This can be a fractional value to pack multiple replicas together on a machine with fewer GPUs than replicas. For example:
```
@serve.deployment(ray_actor_options={"num_gpus": 1})
def func(*args):
    return do_something_with_my_gpu()
```
This will create a deployment where each replica uses a single GPU. If you want to use inter-node model parallelism, you can increase `num_gpus`. However, this requires nodes with multiple GPUs. If the machine does not have the required number of GPUs available, a `RuntimeError` will be thrown by the respective worker. If you set `num_gpus=0`, your policies will be built solely on the CPU, even if GPUs are available on the machine.

